Description:
Inspired contemporary living
Combining period inspired elegance with contemporary entertaining credentials, this three bedroom plus study, two bathroom home is well situated to offer the lifestyle you want. A picturesque entrance introduces a living room with deep cornices and a lofty ceiling, and polished floorboards continue through to the spacious kitchen/dining/family. Equipped with everything from a gas cooktop to a fan forced oven, dishwasher and walk-in pantry, this family hub is linked by glass doors to an entertainer's deck and rear garden with small deciduous trees. Also featuring heating, cooling, electric shutters, an alarm, rainwater tank and wide carport, electronically accessing a rear ROW, the home sees schools, parks, transport and Melville Road within a stroll and cosmopolitan Sydney Road nearby.

Description:
Luxurious High-End Living
Brand-new and beautifully appointed, this stunning two-storey townhouse is set to impress with its premium inclusions, versatile design and exclusive heart-of-Coburg location. Cutting-edge style and quality at every turn, the home's deluxe interior comprises two generous bedrooms with mirrored robes and study/home office, stunning master ensuite and main central bathroom - both with floor-to-ceiling tiles. Add to this a spacious open-plan living/dining area accompanied by a gourmet kitchen complete with stone benchtops/splashbacks, soft-close cabinetry, DeLonghi cooking appliances and Asko dishwasher. Other stand-out features include split-system heating and cooling throughout, alarm and video intercom, LED lighting, double-glazing, European laundry and under-stair storage, plus engineered oak floors and on-trend black fittings throughout. Dual outdoor spaces include a sunny terrace (from the living area) and private rear courtyard with undercover patio, large storage shed and secure off-street parking via remote-control rollerdoor to ROW. Walking distance to Coburg Station and renowned shopping precinct, it's also close to parks and schools, Sydney Road cafes and restaurants, trams to university/hospital precincts as well as easy access to Citylink. Perfect modern living! Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Family Flexibility in a Prime Position
Enjoyed by the one family since new (c1981), this single-level home provides an inner-urban lifestyle of immediate comfort and enviable convenience along with value-adding potential to modernise and possibly expand in the future (STCA). Impeccably-presented interior boasts three bedrooms (larger master with private ensuite), main family bathroom and separate WC. Add to this a spacious lounge and dining room leading through to the open living/meals area and adjoining kitchen. Features include ducted heating, air conditioner, alarm system and a full-size laundry, plus north-facing backyard with undercover patio and ROW potential, as well as a lock-up garage and additional driveway parking space. A short stroll to Robinson Reserve, it also offers easy access to popular primary schools (Coburg West and St Fidelis), Coburg's renowned shopping precinct and Sydney Road cafes, as well as trains and trams to the CBD. Description:
Beautiful Apartment in a Prime Location!
Situated in the historic Pentridge Precinct lies this stunning apartment. With panoramic views of the surrounding suburbs and boasting natural light throughout this feature packed property. Perfectly positioned just a short walk to Public Transport and Coburg Lake. Minutes to vibrant Sydney Road precincts for endless shopping and dining options and easy access to Melbourne CBD as well as major Hospitals and Universities.
Boasting a spacious kitchen/dining with stainless steel appliances including a dishwasher, adjoining onto the living area with polished timber floors, double glazed windows and a split system heating/cooling. The lavish master bedroom comes complete with a walk-in wardrobe, ensuite and your own private balcony well secluded from the rest of the apartment. The generous size second bedroom includes built in wardrobes and serviced by the central bathroom.
Additionally, this property features a European laundry, intercom with security access and egress, storage cage and a separate car space. This property is not to be missed!

Positioned to perfection in a blissfully quiet Coburg neighbourhood, this captivating period home (c1939) provides an oasis of quality and privacy with its Art Deco elegance, tasteful enhancements throughout and delightful backyard surprise. Behind a picture perfect facade, this supremely elegant four bedroom plus studio Californian Bungalow home delivers thoroughly modern living in a tranquil and exclusive cul-de-sac. Sympathetically renovated, displaying the timeless charm of leadlight, fretwork, ornate ceilings and Baltic Pine floors, this expansive home impresses with a free-flowing floorplan where a solid timber island kitchen boasting 800mm Miele cooktop and two Bosch ovens is flanked by formal dining with OFP and generous informal living. Description:
Inner city living with a leafy outlook - A rare find!
Your own townhouse on your own lot (182m2). Private and secure on a corner block, this impeccably maintained townhouse is within an 8 minute walk to Coburg Station and shopping centre. Close to schools, parks and Sydney Road restaurants and café precinct.
So convenient and well presented, it offers 2 bedrooms, study nook, separate lounge and dining area, timber kitchen with modern appliances (Bosch Dishwasher), bathroom (separate shower and bath), separate powder room, laundry and garage with off street parking for 2 cars.
Plenty of comforts including ducted heating, split system air-conditioning, ducted vacuum, alarm, window shutters, intercom and with the option of relaxing in one of your own 3 separate courtyards.

Description:
Classic Style with Immediate Family Appeal
So much more than meets the eye, this captivating Californian Bungalow is sure to surprise with its extended floorplan, quality enhancements and spacious garden surrounds - all in a coveted location with immediate access to the best of Coburg. Impeccably-presented, the home's light-filled interior comprises three genuinely large bedrooms and bathroom with spa, front lounge (or fourth bedroom) and expansive open-plan living/dining area accompanied by a contemporary kitchen complete with tiled splashbacks, soft-close cabinetry, stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher. Additional features include ducted heating and split-system a/c, alarm system, LED lighting, solid timber floors, plus an expansive undercover entertaining area, delightful backyard garden, storage shed and front off-street parking. A prime position walking distance to Sydney Road/Nicholson Street trams, the area's renowned cafes and restaurants, as well as Coburg Station, shops and supermarkets, popular schools, parks and Merri Creek trails.

Description:
Celebration Of Family Living
A celebration of family living this contemporary home arranged over two levels and delivering up to four bedrooms, impresses with its light filled interiors and two expansive living domains. Immaculately maintained, this versatile home boasts a gourmet granite topped timber kitchen, perfectly positioned to service both formal living and dining and informal living domain that flows to alfresco area for effortless entertaining. A sunlit rumpus/fourth bedroom assures space for all the family while quality continues through bedrooms with BIR's, grand master with ensuite, family spa bathroom, heating/cooling, alarm, separate studio plus workshop, and double garage with remote. Ready to enjoy, this exceptional home also sits on approx. 710m2 of prime Residential Zone 1 land, with a short stroll to vibrant Sydney Road, Batman & Coburg Railway Stations, Coburg Lake, Coburg North Primary School, Coburg Farmer's Market, Harmony Park and ease of shopping at Coburg North Village.
For sale in conjunction with Holland & Price

Immaculate throughout with tree top views, the apartment's light and bright interior features two double bedrooms (with built-in robes) and large central bathroom, lounge/meals area complemented by a renovated kitchen with gas cooking and dishwasher. Other highlights include internal laundry facilities, hallway linen cupboard and intercom/secure entry. A brilliant location in cosmopolitan Coburg, it's walking distance to Sydney Road cafes and trams, close to local schools, Coburg Station and the area's renowned shopping precinct.
